### 1. Maven:

Software Project Management Tool (pom.xml)
Automates a JAVA based project

### 2. Talisman:

Pre-Commit, Pre-Push Hooks in GitHub
Checks that potential secrets and sensitive info don't get accidently committed

### 3. Mutation Testing:

PIT runs unit tests against automatically modified code
Mutations are supposed to get killed

### 4. SAST - SonarQube:

Inspection of code

### 5. Vulnerabilities:

Scanning and assessment
NVD, CVE, CVSS, CWE

### 6. Dependency Check:

Evaluates Dependencies

### 7. Trivy:

Vulnerability Scanner for containers and other artifacts

### 8. OPA Conftest:

Policy engine against configuration data
Kubernetes Configurations, Terraform code, Dockerfile or any other config files.

### 9. Kubesec:

Kubernetes security scanner and analysis tool
A single YAML file input, can connect multiple Kubernetes resources

### 10. Integration Tests

Determine if independently developed units of software work correctly when they are connected to each other
Tests the basic correctness of the API by consuming the REST API after it has already been deployed

### 11. DAST - OWASP ZAP

Identifies security vulnerabilities by simulating external attacks on an application while the application is running
OpenAI Specification